Thomas J. Bussey, "What Can Biochemistry Students Learn About Protein Translation? Using Variation Theory to Explore the Space of Learning Created by Some Common External Representations" (PH. D. diss., University of Nevada Las Vegas, 2013). pp. 9-10, fig. 5.<br />
<br />
Ken Johnson, "Paul Durand-Ruel, the Paris Dealer Who Put Impressionism on the Map," New York Times, July 22, 2015 (ill.).<br />
<br />
"Paintings at the Art Institute of Chicago, Highlights of the Collection," (Art Institute of Chicago/Yale University Press, 2017) p. 78.</p>
                  <h2>Ownership History</h2>
      <p>The artist; sold to Durand-Ruel, Paris, November 24, 1893 [Paris 2015]; sold to Harris Whittemore, Connecticut, January 17, 1894 [Paris 2015]; sold by him back to Durand-Ruel, New York, February 4, 1899 [Paris 2015]; sold to the Art Institute, 1910.</p>
          </div>
